I'm not sure what "becoming agentic" means or how it relates to storytelling or debiasing, so I'll provide some context and guidance.

In the context of storytelling and writing, "agentic" refers to giving a character autonomy, agency, and power over their own actions, decisions, and narrative arc. An agentive character is one who takes initiative, makes choices that shape the story, and drives the plot forward. In other words, they're not just passive recipients of events;
